1. Choose Parameters:
    Select values for:
      n = number of trials (e.g., 10)
      p = probability of success (e.g., 0.5)
    Let x = 0 to n (possible number of successes)
2. Create a Table:
    Column A: Values of x from 0 to n.
    Column B: Use the BINOM.DIST function in Excel:
      =BINOM.DIST(x, n, p, FALSE)
3. Plot the Graph:
    Use a bar chart (Insert → Charts → Column Chart) to plot x (horizontal axis) vs probability (vertical axis).
    Label axes: x (Number of Successes) and P(X=x).
4. Add Visual Elements:
    Title: “Binomial Distribution for n = ..., p = ...”
    Gridlines and data labels for clarity.
